# StudyForge Manifest

## Purpose

Privacy-first, offline-first academic PWA. Local LLM inference (WebGPU/WASM), client-side RAG, and optional BYOK cloud fallback. No backend; all compute and storage run in the browser.

## Tech Stack

- **Runtime:** TypeScript strict, React 19, Vite 6, ES modules
- **UI:** Tailwind CSS v4, TipTap, motion, lucide-react, sonner
- **Data:** Dexie 4 (IndexedDB), OPFS for embedding vectors
- **AI:** @wllama/wllama (local), @xenova/transformers (embeddings), hybrid RAG (BM25+RRF)
- **Workers:** PDF parse + embedding pipelines off main thread
- **Tests:** Vitest 4, fake-indexeddb, Testing Library
- **PWA:** vite-plugin-pwa / Workbox

## Architecture Axioms

1. **Client-only** — No server API layer; external calls are direct `fetch` from library components.
2. **Offline-first** — Documents and vectors never leave the device unless user invokes a BYOK provider.
3. **Phase navigation** — `src/App.tsx` switches domain phases; no React Router.
4. **Secrets in vault** — API keys via AES-GCM vault (`src/lib/crypto.ts`), not `.env`. Only `VITE_*` flags in env.
5. **Strict TS** — No `any`; ESLint enforces `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`.

## Directory Map

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/components/phases/` | Domain UI (Planning, Research, Writing, Agents, …) |
| `src/components/library/` | Zotero, Mendeley, PubMed, arXiv integrations |
| `src/lib/` | db, crypto, opfs, rag, useLLM, ai/providers |
| `src/workers/` | pdfWorker, embeddingWorker |
| `src/contexts/` | LanguageContext, SecureConfigContext |
| `src/i18n/` | EN/DE translations |

